      "writtenOn": "2021-05-24T20:37:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Q1. Is Prefix unique across all LUCI projects?\n\nNo\n\n\u003e Q2. IIUC of the following proto, $prefix/$prefixID uniquely identifies each stream. Therefore, $prefix/$prefixID/$streamIndex uniquely identifies each LogEntry across the entire LUCI projects. Let me know if I misunderstood.\n\nPrefix/PrefixIndex should be sufficient:\n  * PrefixIndex is the index of the log entry for the whole prefix; this is shared across all streams within the prefix (so if you alternate writes to stdout/stderr, you\u0027ll get stdout{0 2 4} and stderr{1 3 5}.\n  * StreamIndex is the index of log entries within a stream; starts at 0 and each subsequent write to that stream increments it by one.\n\n\u003e https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/logdog/api/logpb/log.proto\n\u003e \n\u003e I could use $prefix/$name/$streamIndex instead, but I chose to use $prefixID because $prefixID occupies smaller byte space than $name in almost all cases.\n\nwdyt about:\n\n  ${sha(prefix, stream name)}/prefixIndex",
